et Mani, founder of Manichaeism. As a group, Albert Henrichs’ papers on Greek religion offer a basic education on Greek myth and religion and constitute a blueprint for serious study of the subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAncient Greek myth. 0aAncient Greek religion. 0aGods, Greek. 0aGötter. 0aGriechenland ‹Altertum›. 0aGriechisch. 0aLiteratur. 0aMani. 0aMythology, Greek. 0aReligion. 4aGriechenland ‹Altertum›. 4aGriechisch. 4aGötter. 4aLiteratur. 4aMani. 4aReligion. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAncient Greek myth.  aAncient Greek religion.  aGreek gods.  aMani.1 aYunis, Harvey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYunis, Harvey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishz978311061685908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019 Englishz978311061009308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019z9783110605945oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104479270 cprintz978311044665440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311044924240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110449242423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110449242.jpg  a978-3-11-061009-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061685-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-